Class Controller

    • checkAvailability

      public String checkAvailability(int x, int y)
      The function checks if a given coordinate (x, y) is valid on a map and returns a corresponding availability message.
      Parameters:
      x - The x parameter represents the x-coordinate of a location on a map.
      y - The parameter "y" represents the y-coordinate of a location on a map.
      Returns:
      The method is returning a String value. If the coordinates (x, y) are valid on the map, the method will return "Esta disponible" (which means "It is available" in Spanish). Otherwise, it will return "No esta disponible" (which means "It is not available" in Spanish).

    • registerProyect

      public String registerProyect(String researchername, String pilarType, String proyectStatus, String proyectName, String proyectIdentifier, String proyectDescription, Calendar initialDate, Calendar endDate)
      The function `registerProyect` registers a new project with the specified details and adds it to the appropriate pilar based on the researcher's name and pilar type.
      Parameters:
      researchername - The name of the researcher who is registering the project.
      pilarType - The parameter "pilarType" represents the type of pillar that the project belongs to. It can have values such as "biodiversity", "water", "trashcollector", or "energy".
      proyectStatus - The parameter "proyectStatus" represents the status of the project. It could be a string value indicating whether the project is ongoing, completed, or any other status that is relevant to the project management system.
      proyectName - The name of the project that you want to register.
      proyectIdentifier - The proyectIdentifier is a unique identifier for the project. It could be a string or a number that distinguishes one project from another.
      proyectDescription - The proyectDescription parameter is a String that represents the description of the project. It provides additional information about the project, such as its goals, objectives, and any other relevant details.
      initialDate - The initialDate parameter is a Calendar object representing the start date of the project.
      endDate - The endDate parameter is a Calendar object that represents the end date of the project.
      Returns:
      The method is returning a String message. If the project is successfully added, it will return "proyect added successfully". If the researcher name and pilar type do not match, it will return "cannot add proyect if not researcher and a pilar".

    • modifyProyect

      public String modifyProyect(String researchername, String pilarType, String newproyectStatus, String newproyectName, String newproyectIdentifier, String newproyectDescription, Calendar newinitialDate, Calendar newendDate)
      The function modifies a project in a research system based on the provided parameters.
      Parameters:
      researchername - The researcher's name who is modifying the project.
      pilarType - The parameter "pilarType" represents the type of pillar to which the project belongs.
      newproyectStatus - The new status of the project.
      newproyectName - The new name for the project.
      newproyectIdentifier - The new identifier for the project.
      newproyectDescription - The parameter "newproyectDescription" is a String that represents the new description for the project.
      newinitialDate - The new initial date for the project.
      newendDate - The newendDate parameter is a Calendar object representing the new end date of the project.
      Returns:
      The method is returning a String message. If the project with the specified name is found and modified successfully, the message "Proyect modified successfully" is returned. If the project is not found, the same message is returned.

    • registerEvidence

      public String registerEvidence(String evidenceName, String evidenceDescription, String fileURL, String relatedProject, String associatedPointInterest, Calendar registrationDate)
      The function registers evidence by adding it to a project with a matching name.
      Parameters:
      evidenceName - The name of the evidence being registered.
      evidenceDescription - The evidence description is a String that describes the details or characteristics of the evidence being registered. It provides additional information about the evidence to help understand its purpose or relevance.
      fileURL - The file URL is the location or path of the file that contains the evidence. It could be a local file path or a URL to a file stored online.
      relatedProject - The relatedProject parameter is a String that represents the name of the project to which the evidence will be associated.
      associatedPointInterest - The parameter "associatedPointInterest" is a String that represents the point of interest that the evidence is associated with. It could be a specific feature, requirement, or aspect of the project that the evidence is related to.
      registrationDate - The registrationDate parameter is of type Calendar, which represents a specific point in time. It is used to specify the date and time when the evidence is being registered.
      Returns:
      The method is returning a String. If a project with the matching name is found, the method returns "Evidence registered successfully". If no project is found, the method returns "Cannot add evidence if not related to a project".

    • modifyEvidence

      public String modifyEvidence(String evidenceName, String evidenceDescription, String fileURL, String relatedProject, String associatedPointInterest, Calendar registrationDate)
      The function modifies the details of an evidence object in a collection of projects based on the provided evidence name and related project.
      Parameters:
      evidenceName - The name of the evidence that you want to modify.
      evidenceDescription - The evidence description is a string that describes the details or characteristics of the evidence. It provides additional information about the evidence and helps in understanding its purpose or relevance.
      fileURL - The file URL is the URL or path to the file associated with the evidence. It could be a local file path or a URL to a file stored online.
      relatedProject - The relatedProject parameter is a String that represents the name of the project that the evidence is related to.
      associatedPointInterest - The associatedPointInterest parameter is a String that represents the point of interest that is associated with the evidence.
      registrationDate - The registrationDate parameter is of type Calendar, which represents a specific point in time. It is used to set the registration date of the evidence.
      Returns:
      The method is returning a String. If the evidence is found and modified successfully, it will return "Evidence modified successfully". If the evidence is not found, it will return "Evidence not modified".
